    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing nrLDPC_cnProc_BG2_generator_128 function for Zc=128 LDPC processing\n\n### Summary\nUsers attempting to call nrLDPC_cnProc_BG2_generator_128() were getting undefined function errors. The LDPC decoder generator tool was missing this expected function name, even though the functionality existed under a different name.\n\nThis fix adds the missing nrLDPC_cnProc_BG2_generator_128() function that simply delegates to the existing nrLDPC_cnProc_BG2_generator_AVX2() implementation. The main generator program is also updated to call this new function.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_cnProc/cnProc_gen_BG2_avx2.c`: Added nrLDPC_cnProc_BG2_generator_128() function\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_tools/generator_cnProc/main.c`: Updated to declare and call the new function\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Try to call nrLDPC_cnProc_BG2_generator_128() from any code\n2. Observe linker errors about undefined function\n3. With this fix, the function now exists and behaves identically to the AVX2 version\n\nThe fix maintains full backward compatibility while providing the expected function name that users were trying to call.\n"
}